TetR_N Bacterial regulatory proteins, tetR family

Fic Identified by match to PF02661 Fic protein family. cAMP may be a regulation factor in cell division of some bacteria. The Fic (filamentation induced by cAMP) protein is involved in the synthesis of PAB or folate. It would appear that the Fic protein and cAMP are involved in a regulatory mechanism of cell division via folate metabolism and in these organisms cell division could be controlled by coordination of cAMP, Fic and Fts proteins
